<P>The Conver&s;ion of &s;ome of extraor|dinary Guilt now and then, proclaims to the World that this Fountain of his Blood is inexhau&s;tible; that the vertue of it is not &s;pent or drained, tho' &s;o much has been drawn out of it for above Five thou&s;and years already.</P>
<P>And doubtle&s;s, the greater Fruits of this Grace is expected from &s;uch Con|verts in ways of Thankfulne&s;s, Love and Obedience.</P>
